cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper deals with the categorization of natural images using machine learning methods and cognitive models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves human subjects and their cognitive processes, which could place it in cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the use of machine learning models to capture human categorization could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
